<html>
<head>
<script type = "text/javascript">
function changeColor(color) {
}
function SwapData(intCsvFile) {
	document.getElementById("data").DataURL = "data" + intCsvFile + ".csv";
	document.getElementById("data").Reset();
	document.getElementById("mutableData").datasrc="#data";
	return false;
}
function FilterData(strProperty,strFilter) { // e.g. "Gender", "Female"
	document.getElementById("data").Filter = (strProperty) ? strProperty + " = " + strFilter : "";
	document.getElementById("data").Reset();
	document.getElementById("mutableData").datasrc="#data";
	return false;
}
</script>
</head>
<body>
See: <a href = "https://www.599cd.com/tips/hta/advanced/tabulardatacontrol/">https://www.599cd.com/tips/hta/advanced/tabulardatacontrol/</a>
<br />Beware: The TDC (Tabular Data Control) is apparently deprecated starting with MSIE11, but someone has released a jQuery plug-in worth looking into: <a href = "https://datatables.net/">DataTables - Table plug-in for jQuery</a>

<object id="data" classid="clsid:333C7BC4-460F-11D0-BC04-0080C7055A83">
	<param name="DataURL" value="data1.csv">
	<param name="UseHeader" value="True">
	<param name="TextQualifier" value=",">
	<param name="SortColumn" value="LastName;FirstName"><!-- "-" to swap order -->
	<param name="Filter" value="Gender = Male">
</object>

<h2>Customers</h2>
[ <a href = "#" onclick = "return SwapData(1)">CSV Data - Original</a> ]
[ <a href = "#" onclick = "return SwapData(2)">CSV Data - The Shaw Family</a> ]
[ <a href = "#" onclick = "return SwapData(3)">CSV Data - Original</a> ]
<br />
[ <a href = "#" onclick = "return FilterData();">All</a> ]
[ <a href = "#" onclick = "return FilterData('Gender','Male');">Males Only</a> ]
[ <a href = "#" onclick = "return FilterData('Gender','Female');">Females Only</a> ]
[ <a href = "#" onclick = "return FilterData('Gender','F*');">Like F (=F*)</a> ]
<table id = "mutableData" border='1' width='100%' cellspacing='0' datasrc=#data>
<thead>
	<tr>
		<th>First Name</th>
		<th>Last Name</th>
		<th>Gender</th>
	</tr>
</thead>
<tbody>
	<tr>
		<td>
			<div datafld="FirstName"></div>
		</td>
		<td>
			<div datafld="LastName"></div>
		</td>
		<td>
			<b>
				<div datafld="Gender"></div>
			</b>
		</td>
	</tr>
</tbody>
</table>

</body>
</html>